A talented three-year-old girl from north China's Hebei Province has proven herself a born snowboarder after just 12 days of practice. Wang Xixi's impressive skills on the snowy slopes left many fellow ski enthusiasts astounded. At the Qishan Ski Resort in Laiyuan County of north China's Baoding City, the toddler skier always attracts crowds of onlookers as she boldly tackles slopes with apparent ease. Her father acts as a coach, who says snowboarding has unexpectedly brought the family closer together to enjoy the shared passion.